name: 04-Model Training and Validation
content:
Model Training and Evaluation

Model Used:

  • H2O Distributed Random Forest (DRF) – chosen for its ability to handle large, imbalanced datasets and capture nonlinear fraud patterns.

Feature Details:

  • Transaction-based: authzn_amt, acct_curr_bal.
  • Account-based: acct_cl_amt, acct_avl_money_before_amt.
  • Derived: Transaction frequency, utilization ratio, abnormality scores.

Feature Importance:

  • Computed from DRF’s Gini importance. Typically, authzn_amt and acct_avl_money_before_amt are among top predictors of fraud.

Model Metrics:

  • Precision – To reduce false positives.
  • Recall – To ensure fraudulent cases are detected.
  • F1-Score – Balance between precision and recall.
  • ROC-AUC – To assess classification thresholds.
